untrusted comment: Hangar release signing public key (PLACEHOLDER — replace before publishing a release)
RWSxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx==

# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS (one-time, offline on a secured workstation):
#
#   1. Generate the keypair:
#        minisign -G -p keys/hangar-release.pub -s hangar-release.key
#
#   2. Replace the placeholder line above with the content minisign writes to
#      keys/hangar-release.pub (the "untrusted comment" + base64 key lines).
#
#   3. Store hangar-release.key (encrypted) as the GitHub Actions secret MINISIGN_KEY
#      (base64-encode first: base64 hangar-release.key) and store the passphrase as
#      MINISIGN_PASSWORD. Never commit the private key.
#
#   4. Update the HANGAR_PUBKEY constant in install.sh and install.ps1 to match
#      the new base64 public-key string from this file (second line above).
#
#   5. Commit the updated keys/hangar-release.pub and the updated install scripts.
#
# Rotation: generate a new keypair, ship the new public key in install scripts with
# a 90-day transition window while the old key also remains valid in old installs.
